<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Anyway, going back to the my post (which did not intend to inflame all this argument:P), the *optimal* wizard output overtime is slightly less than 350 damage per tic, and yes, that assumes neutral mana, because over a night of exping, your mana must remain neutral.  This is about 50 dps.<P>Now a rogue, at *optimal* output, is 100 dps.  Even if in actuality, he only does half that, he is still doing the same as optimal wizard output, which is *extremely* difficult to maintain.  Since they both are primarily damage dealers, they should have the same output.<P>On top of that, I highly doubt that rogues are cut in half from their optimum under usual circumstances, since all they have to do to maintain optimal output is stay behind the creature, they may take a very small hit for having to evade between stabs (but keep in mind, the backstab button is still refreshing while they evade).<P>A wizard, on the other hand, to maintain 50dps, must always have 4 targets, who enchanters are not mezzing, who the tanks are continually taunting, and not get any resists.  How often do you see that?  I remind you, even if you are correct, the rogue still maintains 50 dps with ease
</FONT>
