I have indicated there is parsed data (from a third source) showing rogue damage at under 50 dps. The other actors in the log gave results which were at least vaguely in line with the expectations I have got from personal parsing -- and to anyone with a vague idea about just how useful a offhand weapon is.<P>Do you have anything similar showing your theoretical rogue dps figure against level-appropriate monsters? Even the time your uber melee groups takes to take down a krup or ili would work, as a sort of Tudamorf-test.<P>And as for wizard dps: if you're taking down four, yes, you can only expect about a 10:1 damage to mana ratio. (In line with my expected rogue damage) If you're taking them down with Jyll's, it is about 2:1 per monster, depending on how many monsters you can cram into a spot. Graffe's site suggests the mid 30s is the top they've managed. I will be experimenting in this vein myself shortly.<P>Safety VonNombre: 53 enchanter<BR>Thaco Table: 45 warrior<BR>Actinic Percussive: 38 wizard<P>--------------------<P>"The AE wizard: when you absolutely have to kill every Mobile Object in the room ... accept no substitute."
