<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
According to your post, a warrior was able to<BR>do 30.9 damage per second under normal circumstances.  I think it's fairly well accepted that rogues are much better damage dealers than warriors.  So how much less than 50 dps can they be?  Wizards have an input of 4-6 mana per second (if they have C2).  *If* they cram a full 4 mobs into each pillar, that's about 50dps, but it is far far more common for them to manage only 4.5:1 damage to mana tops (using dd, rain, and occasional pillars), which is a pitiful ~23 dps by comparison.  On top of that, the melee dps calculations are counting misses, whereas our wizard dps isn't counting resists.  Meaning, the wizard average dps is even lower.<P>Yes, PBAE on masses of mobs is great by all accounts I've heard, but such groups are damned hard to find/put together and train (at least i haven't had any luck getting one).  Wizards need to have a valid role in the standard group lineup and strategy.
</FONT>
