<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Regarding rogue damage:  Rogues need a tank, a tank needs a healer, healer needs mana regen from an enchanter or bard OR a shaman to slow and reduce mob damage.  Without the slow or mana regen the pulls will be slower and exp divided between a larger group of people.  Just an off the cuff analysis but rogues can outdamage wizards considerably but they need a large support staff to do it.  I am ok with it... rangers w/trueshot disc + fleeting quivers + primal bows on the other hand I have MAJOR issues with...<P>You can still play a role but the role is not going to be major damage dealer.  ie you can still snare, stun, aggro off enc/shm/cleric, and evac but don't expect the 20-30% damage to prevail in an exp grind.  If groups need an evac'r they will choose a druid over a wizard for flexibility and if they don't need an evac'r they will choose pretty much any other class over a wizard.  If you want to group at 50+ you better make friends before then at lower levels and prove your worth.<P>Until wizards can augment the damage of other group mates or do more damage over the long run things will just get worse.  As more powerful melee items begin to trickle down to the lower levels even the pre-50 groupability for wizards could be compromised over time.  <P>AE groups, teleports, and quad-kiting are what makes wizards fun.  The rest is just depressing 50+.  Maybe that is enough for some people.  No other class in the game would have a chance in heck of kiting and dropping 4 45th lvl mobs at once in under 2 minutes.  It makes me smile        <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
