<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Daemonn:  The only really worthwhile thing I see on that list is the stunning.  AEs are great...when soloing (not as good as grouping) or in an AE-focused group (good luck finding one).  Snares are ok-ish, but not usually group critical, and don't help efficiency.  Evacs are helpful, but most people I know just go for the rez.  Stuns are very useful.  However, enchanters and clerics do them too, along with having other things (healing, mezzing, etc.) which are far far more useful than our nukes.  But wait, you say, what happens when they run out of mana and can't stun??<P>Does anybody find it depressing that the only reason we get the stunning job is because the only other people who can do it have better things to do with their mana?  Why not just have an extra enchanter, who can also AE stun-lock everything around, for less mana than it costs us to stun-lock one mob, who will also contribute by adding more mezzes to back up the first, and casting all the buffs that the other one can't spare the mana for?<P>Let's face it, the only thing we're really on top of is DD, and as it is now, DD just doesn't stack up to other forms of damage.
</FONT>
