<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Disgruntled Wiz:<BR><STRONG>Well sure, if you completely ignore AE damage, assume rogues will never aggro, epic mob doesn't move around much, and there is an infinite amount of back space.. you are correct.  A rogue is better.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>No, I assume AE damage makes up a small enough component of mob output to be healed, and may hit wizards as well, rogues are better aggro managers than wizards (see below for proof), rogues have plenty of time between backstabs to reposition themself when the mob moves since the backstab button keeps refreshing while you're moving, and the fact that rogues do more than twice the DPS of wizards more than makes up for backspace limitations.<P>*Rogues do damage over time, wizards do it in spurts.  Since aggro has a decay factor, damage over time has a greater DPA (damage per aggro) than spurts.  Furthermore, rogues have evade, which they can do between backstabs without slowing down the refresh of the backstab button.  Wizards get concussion, which is hard to get, costs mana, and may cost you a tic of meditation to stand up and cast.
</FONT>
