For one thing, I don't want to just accept that all the time i've put into my wiz is for naught and just move on.  For another, I don't like being melee, I like standing back with my camera on high, and clicking on stuff that i want to die.<P>Any, the main hurdle of a raid is usually the super mob, not getting to it.  People will make it to the mob just as well with an equal number of members without wizards. 'quick' can only be defined in terms of ratios.  Since a wizards full mana bar of damage is a scratch to an epic mob, there is no concept of 'quick' damage.  And herein lies the fundamental problem, the wizard class is designed to sacrifice damage efficiency for damage speed, and speed is less relevant to exping, and totally irrelevant to epic encounters.  Even the anti-wizard design team at Verant accepts that when it comes to the big encounters, wizards are just plain broken.
