So lets see. A wizard can perform in groups :<BR>-fast damage.<BR>-root.<BR>-snare.<BR>-evac.<P>Fast damage? since we are talking here post 50, fights where groups got rogue+warrior+third melee last less than 40 secs against any average exp mob (frogs, or golems, or skeletons in charasis, etc). What fast damage?? the fight lasts half a minute !!<P>Root? jesus, every body can root : druids, necros, chanters, clerics, rangers, paladins and shamans. Damn sure you will at least have 2 classes in your group who can root.<P>Snare? Wizard's snare is AoE snare. You cant pull with it from a room cuz you prolly agro more mobs. You are in a tight room? yu might snare yourself. And also is more mana expensiv than druids-ranger.<P>Evac? yep, even tho if the group is good you shouldnt need it. Besides druids got it too.<P>Get it right guys. Wizards are all about nukes, that is what they do. Like clerics do heals, shamans do buffs/debuff, warriors tanks, etc. The MAIN feature of the wiz is pure damage. And you CANNOT outdamage a melee throught the evening. Besides they can tank too.<P>Yep, rogues need a warrior, who needs a cleric, who needs mana. Well, wizards needs a warrior too, and neads mana too (do you like you life as a wizzie without C2?). That is call grouping. The alternative is soloing. But since we are here talking about groupin, it is rather obvious than you need fellow companions.<P>And talk about fast damage? Ive seen a 1100 hp backstab. Now how fast is that. And dont forget that rogues can fire up fast damage too if needed: active offensive discipline and see their critics and backstabs fly like hell.<P>--------------------<P>Yaguex, warlock, Paradigm, Solusek Ro.
