<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
What is the point of discussing the theory behind uber encounters?  Just look at any parse of one involving a rogue and wizard, and bane spell or not, the wizard will do less damage.  The *only* parse I have ever seen with a wizard doing more damage is with necros mana-pumping him, and then to be fair you have to divide his damage by 1+(# of necros pumping) since the necros ain't doing anything else.<P>Yes, rogues have difficulties staying behind, have problems with AEs and aggro, but in the end, their base DPS which more than doubles the wizard's over time DPS easily makes up for all of these factors with plenty left to spare.<P>For reference you can look earlier to my post showing over-time wizard dps to be ~23 compared to rogues which was in the upper 40's.<P>And those high AC-level mobs?  Level hurts resists far more than it hurts melee.  Plus there are several uber-resist mobs, and very few, if any, truly uber-AC mobs.
