Sorry, I can't seem to find the link your are mentioning, could you put it up again?<P>Anyway, if we are going to assume lure-use so we can ignore resists, the wizard dps now drops to ~12dps, given clarity 2.  Since a rogue beats this by ~35dps, it will take him less than 3 minutes to catch up.  After which, he will continue to outpace the wizard by about a factor of 4.  Believe you me, 3 minutes is not a very long time.  Plus, if we are going to count the wizard's starting bar, we should count the rogue disciplines as well, which can quadruple damage for 12 seconds, with the possibility of happening to catch one of those mega-backstabs.<P>I should have been more clear about the resists; I was treating lure use as a minimum, and unresisted normal DD a maximum for wizard output, so level hurts in the sense that it lowers the wizard toward having to use lures, with their crappy 12dps.<P>And, for the previous reasons I put up, rogues really don't drop that far from ideal circumstances most of the time, in fact i'd be willing to venture a guess that the damage they lose by having to move around and deal with melee upkeep and all that is less than what wizards lose to resists.
