<A HREF="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=4161.topic&start=1&stop=20" TARGET=_blank>This is the link</A> that Safety posted.<P>And to be honest, I thought your 20 DPS <I>was</I> the raid figure for rogues; I ran my own quick calculation, and a wizard with C2 and cantina of replenishment will do 15-17 DPS (depending on the med rate for 252 meditation), I had assumed the other 4 DPS were from the necro.<P><BR>Bleh, I gotta pay more attention.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Oh, I just remembered another factor; fear/stun. If a wizzie gets feared/stunned (and comes back to the fight), it has less of an effect on his damage rate than if the rogue gets feared/stunned, and to boot the wizard is likely able to stay out of fear/stun range.<P><BR><A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_topic&f=123&t=001503" TARGET=_blank>Here</A> is another interesting thread. It vividly demonstrates the difference being under and over the atk threshold for a particular mob. It holds true for high level combat too (give a caster a blue to whack at vs a low green, you'll see a similar dramatic shift in damage), the only question is whether the uber-mob's AC is high enough to push the ATK threshold high enough sp that your tanks (rogues included) are under the threshold.<P>Arlina
