<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OK - Let's try to focus. And make the issue even more simple.<P>How about the primal group - warrior/cleric/wizzie (which I admit usually only exists early and definitely pre-50)<P>And lets assume the wizzie is not an idiot and overly aggros himself (ie no healing on the wiz)  I think this is fair since idiot wizzies quit early out of frustration.<P>Warrior does 12/18ths damage<BR>Cleric does no damage - heals (gets aggro'd herself!)<BR>Wizzie does 6/18ths damage (yes - half the output of the warrior!!)<P>Even at that pathetic damage output - the wizzie is pulling his weight - his third of the overall effort.  Ask me if the cleric is a broken class, ie what is their DPS?  Their DPS is a composite of the melee characters they can support with heals/buffs. <P>A wizzie's damage contribution is pure and whole, not clouded by what the support cast is doing.  You cannot convince me that a melee's damage contribution is pure, a melee's damage contribution is ALWAYS diluted by the healers/buffers in the group.  A melee's damage contribution cannot and does not stand alone, unless that melee is soloing or in a non-caster group.<P>A wizzie needs no buffs (if played well), he needs no healing (if played well).<P>A Wizzie appreciates the tank, when in a group.  And the tank needs his group, unless he is twinked up the kazoo.  And then that twinked tank does not care about the group dynamic.<P>Think about the truth of the statement - A melee's damage contribution cannot and does not stand alone, unless that melee player is soloing or in a non-caster group.<P>So the rogue does x amount of damage?  Cut that down some because he needs his support cast - which oddly - includes the taunting tank and the cleric in the case of a rogue.<P>My point is this - you just can't appropriately compare the damage contribution between a wiz and a tank without factoring the buffers/healers into the melee equation.  <P>I will be the first to admit, the perception problem is huge.  The idea of consistantly doing less damage than a tank over the exp grind is repugnant.  And to make matters worse, we bellow and whine about it for all to hear.  BUT WE PULL OUR WEIGHT - AND MORE!  We jam dd down throats - and we don't need no stinkin buff to do it either!  <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
